\section{Introduction}

Given $X\sim{}\mbox{Beta}(\alpha, \beta)$, the following is true:
\begin{equation}
E[X] = \alpha / ( \alpha + \beta),
\end{equation}
\begin{equation}
\mbox{var}[X] = \frac{\alpha \beta}{ (\alpha + \beta)^2 (\alpha + \beta +1)}.
\end{equation}

